Question: Do you have any additional ideas, concerns, or feedback you would like to share to help ACME better serve the public?

Response ID: resp_384
Response Text: I love this city so. very. much. After moving around a lot in my 20s, I came to Austin in 2009 and have stayed here longer than I have lived anywhere in my life with the exception of where I grew up (and in a few years I'll "outlive" that). I love the energy and vibe and creativity this city oozes. It's why I stayed even when it was difficult financially. I poured my heart into the ensemble I started right here in Austin in 2011 and just as we were really about to move to the next level Covid hit. As we came out of Covid, I was hopeful that we'd quickly get back to where we were, but then the massive changes to cultural arts funding hit and we were penalized because our board and directors are not BIPoC (the fact that our musician pool is quite diverse didn't matter). The art we present is very directly related to BIPoC cultures/communities, but because of the whiteness of our leadership, we were penalized and shut out of funding. The Latin American music we presented all of the time was in many instances performed nowhere else in the country, and now that we've had to go on long-term hiatus due to funding issues, it's not being played anywhere in the US at all. In light of all that is going on with the arts in this country now, we need all of the arts more than ever. Please help us do our part to guide our community through these scary times by supporting us in our efforts to add some beauty to what is rapidly becoming a very ugly world.

